oh don't get me started on video game music -F

My favorite soundtrack from last year has to be Signs of the Sojourner, which you've said you've played before
sometimes when I feel rattled I just put it on and it always helps a little
Ooh I've never looked into FE music
It's one of my favorite tracks from Fire Emblem. What Fates lacks in gameplay, story, and characters, it vastly makes up for with its superior soundtrack.
I also enjoy lots of other songs from different games. Three Houses has some bangers, Awakening has some emotional pieces, Radiant Dawn has some very atmospheric map themes...
Oh man the Awakening ost was so good

messages.content: It only saves as MP3, right? I'm trying to figure out what audio filetype would be the smallest, I'm assuming .ogg
Yeah that's weird, the audio files are starting late...
I think this is just a VLC thing. I don't know why it does it, though.
I use moobot for playing songs on stream
which allows me to have up to 50 songs in rotation for free (or more for subscription) in a playlist
but also allows song requests on stream (Long as they're youtube)

this means the playlist also uses youtube, however, but doesn't require downloads at all

the only issue with it is sometimes requested songs are skipped, no idea why. messages.content: And it features no visuals from the game so no worries for spoilers
The description also has a lil backstory for the making of this track

> “The first time that I came across the Irish chorus group ANÚNA was from one of their albums released in 1996, called "Deep Dead Blue". Back then I was totally into the music of Northern Europe, including Finland, Ireland, Scotland and the Mediterranean region. Usually world music consists of a land's distinctive instruments, whereas ANÚNA found their way of expression through the human voice, which can be considered the original musical instrument. The album "Deep Dead Blue" really gave me a huge impression, as the chorus wasn’t like a classical one, nor Gregorian, or Bulgarian… I felt that ANÚNA was a new type of chorus that I’d never heard before. My attention was drawn to the lead singer, Michael McGlynn, and I dreamt about making music with ANÚNA one day. After 20 years, my dream came true through the making of the game Xenoblade Chronicles 2. “ – Yasunori Mitsuda

messages.content: bow wow wow, bow wow wow

Does anyone else have heavy music association? I kinda learned this when I was studying in Highschool for a major bio exam that had 200+ questions. 

Our teacher let us listen to music so I listened to the same two albums while I studied for like a month and when I got to the test, BOOM it all was there. 

I find I do it for streaming and work as well. I tried to play a work playlist on use a lot on stream and it kinda fuzzed my brain, haha. 

Just a random Monday morning thought.

I have two I can think of off the top of my head.

1) I played Green Day’s Warning album on loop whenever I played Tony Hawk’s Pro Skater 2.

2) Whenever I build Lego I put on the Sayonara Wild Hearts soundtrack.

messages.content:
Today in Mythic Music Recommendations™:

One of my favorite bands of all time is The Avalanches, an Australian duo who are pioneers of the plunderphonics genre: composing songs entirely (or at least mostly) out of samples of other songs and media.

Their first album, "Since I Left You," premiered in 2000 and totally changed the game of the genre. The album has THOUSANDS of samples, weaving an aural tapestry that sounds unlike anything you've ever heard before. Consider this was all analogue too: they had to physically obtain all these samples and put them together using late 1990's technology.

https://songwhip.com/the-avalanches/since-i-left-you-2

embeds.title: Pinchy & Friends
embeds.description: Pinchy and friends is a mix tape site featuring mixes by an eclectic group of contributors from a variety of creative fields.

messages.content: I got every mix from this website organized into neat little playlists in Winamp 📁, it's good productivity music because it's chill but also like, not the same lo-fi chillhop tunes to study to that I've heard a million times. always eclectic and interesting.

I made this for another discord, but there was talk of 6 favorite albums and I wanted to talk about 6 favorite feelings w/ music and examples of that for me

## WOW, SO KELIFF MUSIC TASTE

I love the prompt! I am going to do my spin on it, which is 6 feelings that I crave in music and examples of those.

### 1 - TAKE ME ON A JOURNEY

I like songs that take you on a **journey**, as in, when there are multiple different sections of the song that feel unique. **Hail The Sun** is *very good at this* imo

- [Secret Wars (Reimagined)](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rg6Og5JOWcQ>) is a favorite of mine
- [Chunker](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YLexasbqt6A>) is more of their traditional style
- Honestly [Wake](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nbb7oa9d7fE&list=PLw21-2ls4hf64GOzOlDddGk1eq4hHgaG_>) is an album I run a lot to
- Musicals are great for this too honestly, [Life is Looking Up](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NoV66UPGX_Q>) by **Forgive Durden** is one *I love*

### 2 - I LOVE SAPPY MUSIC THAT I CAN DAYDREAM TO

- [Everything To Me](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3y1gPtOD1N8>) and [Easier To Love You](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fJ4dKnu2IvY>) from **Porter Robinson**'s new album have been WONDERFULLY SAPPY TO ME

### 3 - I GOT MARRIED TO THIS SONG

I am physically not allowed to skip this song if it comes up on shuffle. It brings me a special heart full feeling.

- [Somewhere Only We Know](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mer6X7nOY_o>) - **Lily Allen**

### 4 - MUSIC FROM EMOTIONAL PARTS OF GAMES

I want to re-live a part of a game where my heart got utterly destroyed? Whoa music is great for that

- [Vignette: Panacea](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DBsNM2h5yNQ>) - **Disasterpiece** - From Hyperlight Drifter. I cried when this song played in the game
- [Heart to Heart](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zd0uYFBf3eA>) - **Beacon Pines**
    - I cried at multiple parts of this game. This scene is one, the ending is another
- *OMORI Spoilers*: || [Final Duet](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ya9EhvcNsA>) HOLY FUCK||

### 5 - MUSIC THAT MAKES ME FEEL LIKE I'M IN A DIFFERENT UNIVERSE

Ethereal music that I can lay on the floor, stare up at the ceiling and imagine different ways my life could have gone

- [White Ball](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bnUZ8HcPKsA>) - **Miracle Musical**
- [My Time](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=erzgjfU271g>) - **Bo En**
    - Specifically the OMORI Trailer version, because that game also fucked me up emotionally (positive)

### 6 - SAD NOSTALGIA

I listened to a LOT of sad music growing up (and I still do). For this feeling, it doesn't need to be a sad song per-se, I just had to be sad while listening to it.

- [At the Bottom of Everything](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2GHyLhbdzN0>) - **Bright Eyes**
- [Shine (Acoustic)](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YXXuG4gxMNY>) - **Muse**
    - I listened to this song on loop when I figured out I was gay and was sad about it
- [I Want to Be Buried In Your Backyard](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-9FDmm_rYjA>) - **Nightmare Of You**

### 7 - BONUS SECTION. SONGS THAT I WILL SING VERY LOUDLY IN THE CAR TO

- [Hannah](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LOyM3xdSurQ>) - **Freelance Whales**
- [The Graveyard Near The House](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PJdZtoZPIhQ>) - **The Airborne Toxic Event**
- [Everything All At Once](<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ftn_xcY-t_I>) - **Local Natives**
I very much relate to mood #1. It is one of the reasons Ayreon has been my favorite thing in music since I was introduced to it.
